text: Baltimore Creek is a stream in Bollinger County in the U.S. state of Missouri. It is a tributary of Little Whitewater Creek.Patton, MO, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1959 (1975 rev.) Baltimore Creek most likely was named after Baltimore, Maryland for unknown reasons. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Bollinger County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
title: Baltimore Creek
